stylometry:
The trade off of a waiting line is to figure out how to balance the cost of waiting in line and the cost of decreasing the wait. 

For example: 
Some people will not wait in line for a product. They would rather sacrifice service or price for less time waiting in line. A manager must ensure that the company is not losing customers to effect profit because they are waiting in line too long. On the contrary a manager must make sure that the company does not have too many workers and is losing money in that aspect. If a company has too many workers it is paying them more than they are making and losing money regardless. There must be a perfect balance to ensure the best profit for the company.
